                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>A small limestone base, intact on all sides, chipped at the bottom of the front. Mouldings to top and bottom of left, front and right faces. The rear is roughly finished and plain, as is the underside. A large ovoid cavity occupies the rear two-thirds of the upper surface 12 cm x 8 cm , and c.1 cm deep</p>
                                    <material n="limestone" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html">limestone
                                    </material>
                                    <objectType n="base" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html">base
                                    </objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">6.6</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">17.6</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">13.6</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>A single line of latin letters occupies the field between the mouldings on the front face; the field is 3.4 cm high x 15.3 cm wide. There is a vacat before the text, and a recessed space after, the surface of the stone being lost.</p>
                                    <rs type="execution" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">Engraved
                                    </rs>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Plain Latin capitals, with minimal serifs; S is fairly tall and shallow; A curves slightly towards the feet; C sits slightly above the line; R is closed, with curving tail.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line1">Line 1</locus>
