            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Carettoni: SACR[-]</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Sacred</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>Carettoni indicated one letter was missing at the end of the text, however the surface is lost and no traces are visible. Were there to be a letter (only A is realistically possible) the inscription would be very poorly aligned, whereas the abbreviation 'sacr(um)' produces a more centred text. The hole on the upper surface is likely to have held the base of a small statue which formed the dedication.</p>
            </div>
